{
  "doc_id": "5307",
  "text": "Our main theorem is that if the method is closed under differentiation, closed under restriction to closed subsystems( to be defined shortly), and preserves quadratic invariants generated by those of the original system, then the method is symplectic when applied to a Hamiltonian system. We then obtain Sanz-Serna's [CITATION_1] and Eirola and Sanz-Serna's [CITATION_2] results concerning symplecticity, as a consequence of quadratic invariant preservation, by verifying that those methods are closed under differentiation and restriction to closed subsytems.",
